=== Setsusha ===
'''Precinct shrine'''
* Kanayama Shrine
* Kashifune Shrine - Enshrines the same deity as {{ill|lt=Kashifune Shrine|Q11543587|qid=Q11543587|1=Kashifune Shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}{{ill|lt=Takatsuki City|Q335423|qid=Q335423|1=Takatsuki}}.
* Takagi Shrine
* Hiyoshi Shrine
* Kumano Shrine
* Inari Hipo Shrine
* Atago Shrine
* Tenmangu Shrine
* Itsukushima Shrine - Deity enshrined: {{ill|lt=Ichikishimahime|Q11059454|qid=Q11059454|lt=Ichikishimahime|1=Ichikishima-hime}}. It is enshrined on a small island in the pond.
* Hyakudayu Shrine - Deities enshrined: Toyowama Tokami, Kushiwama Tokami. <ref name=yuisho/> is located at the entrance to the shrine grounds and is said to be the first shrine you should visit before visiting the head office.

'''{{ill|lt=Otabisho|Q11489117|qid=Q11489117|1=Otabisho}}'''
* Katahara Shrine (Yokomachi, Kameoka City, {{Wiki coordinates|35|00|39.21|N|135|34|51.70|E|region:JP-26|location|name=Katahara Shrine (Otabisho)}})
*: Enshrined in the ruins of a mansion south of Kameyama Castle in the center of Kameoka. Katahara Shrine is a shrine dedicated to the first lord of {{ill|lt=Tamba Kameyama Clan|Q10854981|qid=Q10854981|lt=Kameyama Clan|1=Tanba-Kameyama Domain}}, {{ill|lt=Nobuaki Matsudaira|Q8515964|qid=Q8515964|1=Matsudaira Nobumine}}, and was founded in 1898. Katahara Shrine] (Tamba Shrine [Personal Site]). </ref>. During the annual festival (Kameoka Festival), a mikoshi (portable shrine) is passed to the shrine as a traveling place.* Former Otabisho (Ichi-no-Torii) (Nakayada-cho, Kameoka City, {{Wiki coordinates|35|00|09.39|N|135|34|55.48|E|region:JP-26|location|name=Ichi-no-Torii (Old Otabisho)}})
*: This is where the Otabisho used to be, and currently there is a stone torii (Ichi-no-Torii) built by {{ill|lt=Tadaharu Matsudaira|Q11069865|qid=Q11069865|1=Matsudaira Tadaharu}} in the first year of {{ill|lt=Joo|Q1145081|qid=Q1145081|1=Jōō (Edo period)}} ({{ill|lt=1652|Q6962|qid=Q6962|1=1652}}).

