=== Kameoka Festival ===
The {{ill|lt=regular festival|Q11385469|qid=Q11385469|1=Reisai}} held in October is called ``''{{ill|lt=Kameoka Festival|Q11370928|qid=Q11370928|1=Kameoka Festival}}'''. In ancient times, {{ill|lt=September 25th (lunar calendar)|Q840119|qid=Q840119|lt=September 25th|1=September 25 (Lunisolar)}} was the Shinko Festival, and {{ill|lt=September 30th (lunar calendar)|Q840189|qid=Q840189|lt=30th|1=September 30 (Lunisolar)}} was the Kanko Festival<ref name=kamigami/>.

It is said that the festival at Kuwayama Shrine was abolished by {{ill|lt=Akechi Mitsuhide|Q313320|qid=Q313320|1=Akechi Mitsuhide}} who invaded Tamba, but {{ill|lt=Enpo|Q1145735|qid=Q1145735|1=Enpō}}In 1681|Q7645}}, a mikoshi was donated by the lord of Kameyama Castle, {{ill|lt=Tadaharu Matsudaira|Q11069865|qid=Q11069865|1=Matsudaira Tadaharu}}<ref name=yuisho/>, and since then, the annual festival has been known as the Kameyama Festival (later Kameoka Festival), the largest festival in Kouchi-Tamba, and based on tradition, oak boats have also been paraded around the festival <ref>[http://www.k-yamahoko.com/history.html History of Yamahoko Events] ([http://www.k-yamahoko.com/index.html Kameoka Festival Homepage]) </ref>.

At the festival, 11 floats are paraded like the {{ill|lt=Gion Festival|Q979873|qid=Q979873|1=Gion Matsuri}} at {{ill|lt=Yasaka Shrine|Q692714|qid=Q692714|1=Yasaka Shrine}} in Kyoto, and mikoshi from both Kuwayama and Hachimangu Shrines are carried to Katahara Shrine, the Otabisho.

=== Cultural assets ===

=== Kyoto prefecture registered cultural property ===
*Tangible cultural property
** Kuwayama Shrine and the Hachiman Shrine main hall (structure) - Registered on April 15, 1983 (Showa 58).
* Intangible folk cultural assets
** Kameoka Festival Yamahoko Event - The protection organization is the Kameoka Festival Yamahoko Association. Registered on March 19, 2004.

=== Kyoto Prefecture Cultural Properties Environmental Conservation District ===
* Kuwayama Shrine Cultural Property Environmental Conservation District - Decided on May 15, 1985.

=== Cultural property designated by Kameoka City ===
* Intangible folk cultural assets
** Kameoka Festival Yamahoko Event - The protection organization is the Kameoka Festival Yamahoko Association. Designated on August 3, 1998.

